<chapter xml:id="ch-PS" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Power Series (PS)</title>

  <objectives>
    <introduction>
      <p>
        This module describes power series- how to find them, and use them to approximate functions.
      </p>
    </introduction>
      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>PS1</title>
          <p>
            I can determine the radius and interval of convergence of a power series.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>PS2</title>
          <p>
            I can use properties of work with and represent power series by addition, subtraction, multiplication, differentiation, or integration
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>PS3</title>
          <p>
            I can compute the Taylor or Maclaurin series of a function, centered at a given input
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
  </objectives>
  
